oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Camp Myles campsite
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Sepia photograph of six unidentified people gathered at a wooded campsite at Camp Myles. There are multiple tents pitched behind them. On one of the tents is a sign that reads "Camp Myles." Features a divided back and handwritten note on reverse. Logo around the stamp area in the upper right corner indicates this postcard was printed on Eastman Kodak photographic paper.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: Camping; Tents; People; Forests
